  "prompt": "What is an example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users?",
  "response": "A classic example is Spotify using Facebook's platform in its early days. When Spotify first launched in the United States, users could only sign up by logging in through their Facebook account. This allowed Spotify to:\n\n1. Quickly verify user identities\n2. Automatically import user social graphs\n3. Leverage Facebook's massive user base\n4. Reduce friction in the sign-up process\n\nBy integrating with Facebook, Spotify gained instant credibility and made it easy for users to join and share music, which helped drive rapid user acquisition.\n\nOther examples include:\n- Airbnb using Craigslist to initially find hosts\n- Instagram leveraging Facebook's social graph\n- Tinder using Facebook for user authentication and profile data\n- Zynga games using Facebook's platform in the early days of social gaming",
